caption: Hamza Igamane is a cult hero. The Old Firm derby has a soft spot for producing classic moments, and this one is due to go platinum. Came off the bench in the 83rd minute. Bagged the winner just five minutes later. Real hitman settings. Secured Rangers’ first league win at Celtic Park in four years. The Moroccan Morelos is mashing work. You’re looking at a proper bagsman who can rise to the occasion and rise it when it truly matters. Pulled up to the opp block and got to chopping. Call this baller the couscous McCoist the way he led Celtic fans down a blind Ally. But let’s talk about that finish. Minimal backlift, but the power could’ve moved the Atlas Mountains. A winner so cold, it had Václav Černý spraying his drink on the home fans like Steve Austin. Igamane is HIM.
